    <!-- ─── Section 11: Modern Qt6 ─── -->
    <section id="qt6" class="mb-24 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="display text-3xl font-medium mb-4">Modern Qt6 Idioms</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Qt6 introduced several features that eliminate boilerplate and enable new patterns.
        If you're starting a new project, use all of these.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-medium text-sm mb-2">Bindable properties (no signals needed)</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-xs mb-3">Qt6's <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-cream px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">QProperty&lt;T&gt;</code> enables reactive bindings in pure C++ — the same concept as QML property bindings, but on the C++ side.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <pre class="font-mono text-xs text-muted bg-cream p-4 rounded-lg"><code set:html={codeBindable}></code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-medium text-sm mb-2">QStringView / QLatin1StringView</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-xs mb-3">Pass read-only string parameters by value without allocation. <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-cream px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">QStringLiteral</code> for compile-time string construction.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <pre class="font-mono text-xs text-muted bg-cream p-4 rounded-lg"><code set:html={codeStringView}></code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-medium text-sm mb-2">QCoro for async/await (third-party)</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-xs mb-3">Write asynchronous code that reads like synchronous code using C++20 coroutines. Gaining traction in the Qt community.</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <pre class="font-mono text-xs text-muted bg-cream p-4 rounded-lg"><code set:html={codeQCoro}></code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
